#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:5
msgid "Emscripten Contrib Ports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:7
msgid ""
"Contrib ports are contributed by the wider community and supported on a "
"\"best effort\" basis. Since they are not run as part of emscripten CI they "
"are not always guaranteed to build or function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:11
msgid ""
"The following is the complete list of the contrib ports that are available "
"in emscripten. In order to use a contrib port you use the ``--use-"
"port=<port_name>`` option (:ref:`emcc <emcc-use-port>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:18
msgid "contrib.glfw3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:20
msgid ""
"This project is an Emscripten port of GLFW written in C++ for the web/"
"webassembly platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Contrib-Ports.rst:24
msgid ""
"Emscripten includes support for both GLFW 2 and 3 written in Javascript. "
"These can be activated with the :ref:`settings <use_glfw>` ``-sUSE_GLFW=2`` "
"and ``-sUSE_GLFW=3``. This non-official contribution, written in C++, "
"provides a more extensive and up-to-date implementation of the GLFW 3 API "
"than the built-in port. It is enabled with the option ``--use-port=contrib."
"glfw3``."
msgstr ""

